1
00:00:00,334 --> 00:00:02,375
Here there used to be a desk

2
00:00:04,042 --> 00:00:06,375
You wanted a baptism certificate for example

3
00:00:06,417 --> 00:00:07,959
You came here and asked the priest for a baptism certificate

4
00:00:07,959 --> 00:00:10,042
Or a death certificate and so on

5
00:00:10,042 --> 00:00:11,042
It was from here

6
00:00:11,083 --> 00:00:14,709
An office room where he wrote whatever information you needed

7
00:00:14,709 --> 00:00:15,709
For marriage for example

8
00:00:16,459 --> 00:00:19,876
Marriage or divorce certificates, all of that was here

9
00:00:20,250 --> 00:00:21,959
Here, the desk was here

10
00:00:22,751 --> 00:00:23,792
In this place

11
00:00:24,792 --> 00:00:26,459
Interviewer: And the rest of the room?

12
00:00:26,751 --> 00:00:28,292
Witness: A place to sit

13
00:00:29,125 --> 00:00:31,918
For example you came to get a baptism certificate

14
00:00:32,459 --> 00:00:34,792
So you sat instead of staying standing, everyone sat

15
00:00:35,209 --> 00:00:37,959
And there was the chair of the archbishop

16
00:00:38,250 --> 00:00:40,375
The head of the Armenian community in Iraq

17
00:00:40,626 --> 00:00:41,626
There opposite him

18
00:00:42,459 --> 00:00:44,125
But here it was all chairs

19
00:00:48,083 --> 00:00:50,250
Interviewer: The chair you told us about, where was it?

20
00:00:50,250 --> 00:00:51,292
Witness: Here, in the middle

21
00:00:51,792 --> 00:00:55,417
Interviewer: What is this?
Witness: This was the place of the archbishop, the head of the Armenians

22
00:00:55,959 --> 00:00:57,542
The head of the Armenians, he sat here

23
00:00:58,042 --> 00:01:00,709
Also two small chairs, to the right and left

24
00:01:01,292 --> 00:01:02,626
Priests sat with him

25
00:01:02,918 --> 00:01:04,000
Because he was of higher rank

26
00:01:05,125 --> 00:01:07,417
It was a council, everyone who came sat there

27
00:01:07,417 --> 00:01:09,834
Interviewer: What did the chair look like, was it ordinary?

28
00:01:09,834 --> 00:01:11,417
Witness: A presidential chair here

29
00:01:11,584 --> 00:01:13,083
In the middle a presidential chair

30
00:01:13,876 --> 00:01:16,042
Interviewer: Was the chair built in?

31
00:01:16,042 --> 00:01:18,959
Witness: No, it was wooden but first class

32
00:01:19,709 --> 00:01:21,792
It was beautiful and had a cross sign on it

33
00:01:21,834 --> 00:01:22,834
It was something beautiful

34
00:01:22,959 --> 00:01:26,505
It was not something ordinary
